sc0 ls0 ws0">VERYTHING IN HUMAN LIFE AND HUMAN HISTORY,&quot; </div><div class="t m205 x3f h1c ya7f ff5 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">wrote Reinhold Niebuhr, &quot;moves toward an end.&quot; He is right. </div><div class="t m4e8 x3f h1c ya7d ff5 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Whether sooner or whether later, </div><div class="t m2b7 xb5 h1c ya7d ff8 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the </div><div class="t m19e x29 h1c ya7d ff5 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">end, or at least </div><div class="t m248 xc7 h1c ya7d ff8 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">an </div><div class="t m26b x4c h1c ya7d ff5 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">end, is </div><div class="t m462 x10 h1c ya80 ff5 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">coming. As Christians, we know what that end is. And even if we </div><div class="t m763 x10 h1c ya81 ff5 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">don&apos;t know when the end will come, we know how it will come and </div><div class="t m224 x10 h1c y95c ff5 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">why it ends as it does. That is why we have such a great hope, because </div><div class="t m78 x10 h1c y5cf ff5 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">not only do we know how it will end, we also know the promise—</div><div class="t m798 x10 h1c ya82 ff5 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">sealed with &quot;the death of the testator&quot; (Heb. 9:16)—that will be </div><div class="t m4bc x10 h1c ya83 ff5 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">unfurled and presented at the end, the promise that we shall &quot;meet the </div><div class="t m5fc x10 h1c ya84 ff5 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Lord in the air: and so shall we ever be with the Lord&quot; (1 Thess. 4:17). </div><div class="t m30d x10 h1c ya85 ff5 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">It does not get any better than that! </div><div class="t m2c2 x10 h1c y950 ff5 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">*Please study this week&apos;s lesson to prepare for Sabbath, Dec. 28. </div><div class="t m49f x10 h1c ya86 ff5 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">104 </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
